This paper discusses the design of a new Wi-Fi standard for IoT communications, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of OFDM, which is a common technique in information theory (cs.IT). The paper proposes an asymmetric design, which involves pushing decoding burdens to the AP side, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) and control engineering (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the reduction of TX power, which falls under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE).
